### Overall Behavior Rules
- Always proceed to next sequential step unless explicitly indicated to skip ahead. Proceed sequentially even if going back to a previous step.
- **Step 6 may only be entered when the user explicitly types "RUN" at Step 5b. When the user selects options A–H at Step 5b, the workflow returns to Step 3 and must proceed sequentially through every subsequent step (Steps 3 → 4 → 5 → 5b) before stopping at Step 5b for user input again. No step may be skipped and Step 6 must never be triggered automatically.**

