#### B. Risk Score Calculation

**Tiers & Point Values**

| Tier | Points Each | Max | Codes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Critical | 10 | 170 | BLK, BRB, BUS, DEN, FOF, FOS, FRD, IRC, MLA, ORG, PEP, REG, SEC, SEX, SNX, TER, WLT |
| Valuable | 5 | 115 | CFT, CYB, DTF, ENV, FUG, GAM, HUM, IMP, KID, LMD, LNS, MOR, MSB, MUR, OBS, PRJ, RES, SMG, SPY, TAX, TFT, TRF, VCY |
| Investigative | 3 | 27 | ARS, AST, BUR, CON, DPS, FOR, IGN, PSP, ROB |
| Probative | 1 | 5 | ABU, CPR, IPR, MIS, NSC |
| **Theoretical Maximum** | | **317** | |

**Scoring Method**

- **Related party score:** Sum points for all flagged codes. Normalize: (raw score ÷ 317) × 100 = score (0–100)
- **Client score:** Same method as related parties. Calculated and displayed separately from the group score
- **Group score:** max(client score, highest related party score) + log(n) × modifier, where n = number of related parties with any flags and modifier = 5–10 (tunable). Cap at 100

**Risk Levels**

| Level | Range |
|---|---|
| 🔴 High (red text) | 67–100 |
| 🟠 Medium (orange text) | 34–66 |
| 🔘 Low (grey text) | 0–33 |

Applied independently to client score, each related party score, and group score.

**Core Rules**
- All code additions are additive only — no code can reduce a score
- A lower-tier flag never offsets a higher-tier one
- Adding related parties never reduces group risk
- Client score and group score are always displayed separately

**Display / Communication Guidelines**
- Do not show the detailed math of the calculation
- Only provide high-level information focused on the client and related party event categories that significantly increase overall risk
- Keep commentary targeted to the most influential risk events

